## Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

```{r pressure, echo=FALSE}
plot(pressure)
```

Note that the `echo = FALSE` parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

##Generating Graph comparing cost of living and minimum ticket price (trendline)



```{r}

Usable_COL_Ticket_Data <- Final_Ticket_Data_COL[-c(1464, 1465, 1466, 1467),]
View(Usable_COL_Ticket_Data)

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(Usable_COL_Ticket_Data, aes(Cost_of_Living_Index, Minimum_Ticket_Price)) + geom_point() +ylim(0,275)
      

```
